"meanings":["From an Old English female personal name derived from <i>ēad</i> ‘prosperity, riches’ + <i>gӯð</i> ‘strife’. This was borne by a daughter (  961–984 ) of Edgar the Peaceful. (She was named in accordance with the common Old English practice of repeating name elements within a family.) She spent her short life in a convent, and is regarded as a saint."],"variants":[{"name":"Edyth","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Edith ."]},{"name":"Edythe","meanings":["From an Old English female personal name derived from <i>ēad</i> ‘prosperity, riches’ + <i>gӯð</i> ‘strife’. This was borne by a daughter (  961–984 ) of Edgar the Peaceful. (She was named in accordance with the common Old English practice of repeating name elements within a family.) She spent her short life in a convent, and is regarded as a saint."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Edith Constable was born in 1225, in Hillmorton, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Sir Thomas de Astley."},"et":{"1225–":"1225–Surnud","1215–1265":"1215–1265","1252–Male":"1252–Surnud","1254–Female":"1254–Surnud","1260–1347":"1260–1347","1225–Female":"1225–Surnud","1347":"1347","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1254":"1254","1265":"1265","1252":"1252","1260":"1260","Astley, Warwickshire, England":"Astley, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hillmorton, Warwickshire, England":"Hillmorton, Warwickshire, England","Astley, Warwick, England":"Astley, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1225–":"1225–Kuollut","1215–1265":"1215–1265","1252–Male":"1252–Kuollut","1254–Female":"1254–Kuollut","1260–1347":"1260–1347","1225–Female":"1225–Kuollut","1347":"1347","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1254":"1254","1265":"1265","1252":"1252","1260":"1260","Astley, Warwickshire, England":"Astley, Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hillmorton, Warwickshire, England":"Hillmorton, Warwickshire, England","Astley, Warwick, England":"Astley, Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"f